<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1223> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1223" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 44f., 117, 438f." ;
	dprr:hasID 1223 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1197> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1197" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Forbidden by the Pont. Max. to leave the city in 242 (see above, Consuls)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1197 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1195> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1195" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Polyb. 1.59.8; Diod. 24.11; Varro Vit. P. R. in Non. 887 L, and Nep. Hamilc. 1.3, on Catulus; Liv. Per. 19; Liv. 22.14.13; 23.13.3-4; 37.51.1-2; Flor. 1.18.33; Eutrop. 2.27; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.17, on Catulus; Degrassi 42f., 117, 436f. Catulus, with the Praetor as colleague, received command of a new fleet, and though wounded at Drepanum, won the decisive naval engagement on March 10, 241, at the Aegates islands (Polyb. 1.59.8-61; Varro Vit. P. R. in Non. 887 L; Diod. 24.11; Nep. Hamilc. 1.3; Liv. Per. 19; 22.14.13; 23.13.3-4; 28.38.9, and 41.3; 45.38.4; Val. Max. 2.8.2; Sil. Ital. 6.684-8; Flor. 1.18.33-37; Eutrop. 2.27, with date; Ampel. 46.3; Oros. 4.10.4-8; Zon. 8.17; cf. Ined. Vat., Hermes 27 [1892] 122). Postumius, who was Flamen Martialis, was forbidden by the Pontifex Maximus to leave the city (Liv. Per. 19; Liv. 37.51.1-2; Val. Max. 1.1.2; Tac. Ann. 3.71)." ;
	dprr:hasID 1195 .
